  "read": "TileLang sparse-MLA backward probability recompute sink with per-route selected-limit metadata. It consumes real q/dO/output/lse plus compressed KV and packed group ids, computes dO.output once per token, recomputes QK and dO.KV once per token/selected tile, then writes a tiny [route_tiles, H] checksum of P plus scaled dP. It intentionally does not compute dKV; this isolates whether the next two-level dKV schedule can afford P/dP recompute once before reusing those values across D blocks. This run feeds real TorchTitan sparse-MLA boundary tensors into the TileLang dKV producer. Materialized per-head probs and scaled grad_logits are present only for materialized-input modes or correctness-reference checks; recompute mode uses q/dO/output/lse/compressed KV in the timed producer.",
